o PRSFTY010: HCl Emergency Equipment Checks Form;

    The purpose of this procedure is to document the HCl Emergency Equipment to be checked per PRSFTY010.

o PRSFTY01: Routine Management of the HCL Process;

    The purpose of this procedure is to outline the routine management of the aHCl process to ensure compliance to OSHA's Process Safety Management (PSM) rule 20 CFR 1910.119 and EPA's rule for Risk Management Plan (RMP) 40 CFR Part 68

o PRSFTY012: Process Safety Management;

    The purpose of this document is to ensure compliance Florida Accidental Release Prevention and Risk Management Planning Act (Chapter 252, Part IV) and the US Environmental Protection Agency's Chemical Accident Prevention Provisions (40 CFR part 68); by instituting a Process Safety Management (PSM) system to ensure that the appropriate procedures, personnel, and equipment to prevent an accidental release of anhydrous Hydrogen Chloride (AHCl) are in place and functioning effectively.

